SIMPLE: squander
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squander
<hw>Squan"der</hw> <pr>(skw⟦ocr⟧n"d⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Squandered</conjf>
<pr>(-d⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Squandering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Scot.
<ets>squatter</ets> to splash water about, to scatter, to squander,
Prov. E. <ets>swatter</ets>, Dan. <ets>sqvatte</ets>, Sw.
<ets>sqv⟦aum⟧tta</ets> to squirt, <ets>sqv⟦aum⟧ttra</ets> to squander,
Icel. <ets>skvetta</ets> to squirt out, to throw out water.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To scatter; to disperse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>squandered</qex> troops he rallies.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To spend lavishly or profusely; to spend prodigally
or wastefully; to use without economy or judgment; to dissipate; <as>as,
to <ex>squander</ex> an estate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The crime of <qex>squandering</qex> health is equal to the
folly.</q> <rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To spend; expend; waste; scatter;
dissipate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squander</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squander
<hw>Squan"der</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To spend lavishly;
to be wasteful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They often <qex>squandered</qex>, but they never gave.</q>
<rj><qau>Savage.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To wander at random; to scatter.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wise man's folly is anatomized⟦br⟧
Even by <qex>squandering</qex> glances of the fool.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squander</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Squander
<hw>Squan"der</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of squandering;
waste.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squanderer</ent>⟦br⟧
